p: The data in this study are similar to data reported for the city of São José do Rio Preto, Brazil. In 2016, that city experienced a dengue outbreak characterized by the co-circulation of DENV-1 and DENV-2 and infections with concurrent ZIKV ( 16). This created epidemiological conditions for the coinfections. In this outbreak, 12 cases of coinfection by DENV and ZIKV were identified.
